BODY. Margins are parallel; the anterior extremity is pointed; the posterior, rounded (
Fig. 6A
). The dorsum is slightly convex; the ventral side flattened (
Fig. 6B
). The dorsum is dark orange-brown; the body margins are orange. A narrow clear grey stripe extends along the entire body length, except for the very anterior and posterior body tips. The ventral side is ivory in color.
